result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Justin Allen Kulinski was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Justin Allen Kulinski was found guilty of Operate Firearm While Intoxicated, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Justin Allen Kulinski in court with attorney Michael M. Hayes.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

AS TO COUNT ONE: 

Defendant waived rights and pled guilty.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Parties stipulate to the facts of the complaint as a basis for a guilty plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the complaint.  Judgment of Conviction entered.

ON MOTION OF THE STATE, COURT ORDERED COUNT TWO:  DISMISSED. 

Court withheld sentence, but granted defendant credit for 6 DAYS time served in the event that sentence is imposed at a later date.  Court placed defendant on probation for ONE YEAR AFTER THE COMPLETION OF COUNT 3 ,  with the following conditions: 
CONDITIONS 
complete sobriety
*45 days  condition time , straight and concurrent to count three
* AODA assessment and follow through with recommended programming.
* Defendant's operating privilege for operation of Class D vehicles is restricted to operating vehicles that are equipped with an ignition interlock device; and each motor vehicle for which the defendant's name appears on the vehicle's certificate of title or registration must be equipped with an ignition interlock device beginning on the date the department issues any license and for a period of  TWO YEARS  thereafter. 

Court ordered defendant's operating privileges revoked for 3 YEARS  with the mandatory reinstatement fee.

Fine of $1800. 00 PLUS ALL MANDATORY COSTS, FEES AND SURCHARGES  costs to be paid by 11-23-18 or serve 60 CONSECUTIVE days in the House of Correction.

Court will revisit the IID exemption after defendant has made some payments towards the fine. 


Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
WCS Intoxicated Driver Intervention program report, received and filed.
Court set bail in the amount of $200.00 cash for the remaining counts 1 and 2.

Defendant Justin Allen Kulinski in court with attorney Michael M. Hayes.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. WCS report received and filed. 

AS TO COUNT THREE: 

  Defendant waived rights and pled guilty.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Parties stipulate to the facts of the complaint as a basis for a guilty plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the complaint.  Judgment of Conviction entered.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

 The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 1day time served. NO Huber privileges.   Sentence to commence forthwith.   If defendant installs an IID court will grant huber privileges. 

Fine of $1300.00  including  all mandatory costs, fees and dna surcharge to be paid from bail on deposit
